# Environment Template

Copy this file to `.env` and update with your actual values.

```bash
# ==================== DATABASE ====================
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_password_here
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=customer_360

# ==================== MLFLOW ====================
# File-based tracking (development)
MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=file:///D:/Project/360Customer/ml/mlruns

# Or use database backend (production recommended)
# MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mlflow

# ==================== API ====================
API_HOST=0.0.0.0
API_PORT=8000

# ==================== DATA PATHS ====================
PREDICTIONS_PATH=/app/predictions.csv
FEATURE_IMPORTANCE_PATH=/app/feature_importance.json

# ==================== LOGGING ====================
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_FILE=logs/app.log

# ==================== AIRFLOW ====================
AIRFLOW_HOME=/airflow
AIRFLOW__CORE__DAGS_FOLDER=/airflow/dags
AIRFLOW__CORE__LOAD_EXAMPLES=False

# ==================== DBT ====================
DBT_PROFILES_DIR=~/.dbt
DBT_TARGET=dev

# ==================== ENVIRONMENT ====================
ENVIRONMENT=development
# Options: development, staging, production

# ==================== DEBUG ====================
DEBUG=True
# Set to False in production
```

## Important Notes

- **Never commit the actual `.env` file** - it contains secrets
- Use this template as reference
- Update values for your environment
- For production, use environment-specific variables
- Store secrets in a secure vault (AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
